# rvnu — Netlify routing
# The site root ("/") serves the temporary holding page (index.html).
# The previous homepage has been removed; /en now points at the holding page.

# Old homepage is retired — force /home.html to the holding page even if a
# stale file lingers in the deploy ("!" shadows any matching static file).
/home.html       /                301!
/home            /                301!

# Bilingual entry points
/en              /                200
/ar              /ar.html         200

# Brand styleguide (so we can share /brand instead of /brand.html)
/brand           /brand.html      200

# Tolerate trailing-slash and .html-suffix variants
/en/             /                200
/ar/             /ar.html         200
/brand/          /brand.html      200
/brand.html      /brand           301

# Brand kit downloads — short aliases for the long canonical filenames
/brand/guidelines.pdf      /brand/rvnu-visual-identity-2026.pdf  200
/brand/identity.pdf        /brand/rvnu-visual-identity-2026.pdf  200
